PlanetarySystem.name: Juno System
PlanetarySystem.author: Jundroo
PlanetarySystem.Description: The default planetary system for the game.

PlanetarySystem.name: Juno System (Classic)
PlanetarySystem.author: Jundroo
PlanetarySystem.Description: This was the default planetary system for the game when it first launched in Early Access on Steam in November of 2018. It consists of a star named Juno, an Earth-like planet named Droo, its moon Luna, a Mars-like planet named Cylero, and two gas giants named Tydos and Urados.

PlanetarySystem.name: Planet Studio
PlanetarySystem.author: Jundroo
PlanetarySystem.Description: The new planetary system for the game.

CelestialBody.name: Boreas
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A cold solid planet covered in partially cracked ice and many crater impacts.

CelestialBody.name: Brigo
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A small rocky moon covered in ice, with horizontal cracks surrounding the surface and an enormous crater near the north pole.

CelestialBody.name: Cylero
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A reddish rocky planet with a thin atmosphere, covered in craters, volcanoes and large valles.

CelestialBody.name: Cylero
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A reddish-brown terrestrial planet with a thin atmosphere. The planet has ice caps at the northern and southern poles. One of the most prominent features of the planet is the basin covering a large portion of the northern hemisphere. Many craters litter then landscape, though few are found in the northern basin. The planet is home to many large highland and lowland plains. Ancient volcanoes can also be found beyond the northern basin.

CelestialBody.name: Droo
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky planet with vast oceans, very diverse biomes and a dense atmosphere, covered in what seems to be vegetation.

CelestialBody.name: Droo
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A terrestrial planet with an atmosphere and capable of supporting life. Much of the planet is covered by vast oceans, grasslands, and forests. Many large deserts exist near the equator. A giant ice sheet covers the southern pole, while the northern pole consists mostly of freezing water and some icy terrain. Mountain ranges can be found all over the surface of the planet.

CelestialBody.name: Handrew's Comet
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: An ice comet with a very rough shape.

CelestialBody.name: Herma
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A small rocky moon covered in orange dust.

CelestialBody.name: Hypatchion
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: An elongated rock covered in craters. It looks very similar to one of the moons found in the Solar System, if my memory doesn't fail.

CelestialBody.name: Jastrus
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A small icy moon that is part of the rings of Urados. Some say judging on the name you would expect more crater passes.

CelestialBody.name: Juno
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A giant natural fusion reactor covered in insanely hot blue flames.

CelestialBody.name: Juno
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: The massive star at the center of the planetary system.

CelestialBody.name: Luna
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A gray rocky moon covered in countless craters of all sizes. The moon is home to a few vast mares that may have been formed by ancient volcanic eruptions.

CelestialBody.name: Luna
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A gray rocky moon covered in countless craters of all sizes. The moon is home to a few vast lowland plains that may have been formed by ancient volcanic eruptions.

CelestialBody.name: Miros
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky moon with an elevated ring around its equator and two clear regions surrounding its surface, one covered in ice and the other in naked rock.

CelestialBody.name: Nebra
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky planet with geothermal activity preventing its surface water from freezing and causing it to evaporate, creating a thick pink atmosphere.

CelestialBody.name: Niobe
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A tiny captured asteroid with smooth ice plains and boulder fields.

CelestialBody.name: Orcus
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A mysterious icy moon with very rough pink ice poles and softer blue and orange ice fields covered in long cracks.

CelestialBody.name: Sergeaa
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky planet with a very thick atmosphere and a very rough surface with lava lakes and volcanoes.

CelestialBody.name: T.T.
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A dark metallic object from interstellar space captured on a retrograde orbit on the edge of the Droo system. Although the hardest to see and to reach, this moon could be the one hiding the most intriguing secrets.

CelestialBody.name: Taurus
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A big moon with an incredibly thick atmosphere and large methane oceans.

CelestialBody.name: Gas Giant 2
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A tilted gas giant with smooth bands and a series of rings.

CelestialBody.name: Gas Giant
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A ringless gas giant with a very chaotic top layer of clouds and enormous storms.

CelestialBody.name: Ice
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A cold solid celestial body covered in partially cracked ice and many crater impacts.

CelestialBody.name: Lava
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky celestial body covered in cracks containing rivers of lava with a very irregular crust.

CelestialBody.name: Lunar
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky celestial body covered in fine regolith and craters, with some signs of volcanic activity.

CelestialBody.name: Martian
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky celestial body covered in dust and craters, with enormous volcanoes and pronounced valles.

CelestialBody.name: Ocean
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky celestial body with geothermal activity preventing its surface water from freezing.

CelestialBody.name: Rock
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rock so small that it can't maintain a spherical shape.

CelestialBody.name: Star
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A giant natural fusion reactor covered in flames.

CelestialBody.name: Terrestrial
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky celestial body with vast oceans, very diverse biomes and a dense atmosphere, covered in what seems to be vegetation.

CelestialBody.name: Venusian
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky celestial body with a very thick atmosphere and a surface with very extreme conditions.

CelestialBody.name: Tydos
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A ringless gas giant with a very chaotic top layer of clouds and enormous storms, very colorful bands and a very thick atmosphere.

CelestialBody.name: Tydos
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: An enormous gas giant with a colorful striped appearance.

CelestialBody.name: Urados
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A blue gas giant with soft bands and a ring system normal to its rotation axis.

CelestialBody.name: Urados
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A large gas giant with blue/white stripes and a ring system.

CelestialBody.name: Vulco
CelestialBody.author: Jundroo
CelestialBody.Description: A rocky planet tidally locked to its star, with a face fully melted and the other covered in rivers of lava and a very irregular crust.
